#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn11.13"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.13:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.13:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga "
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 13. Mahālisutta → mahāli (sattavatapada) suttaṃ (bj) | devasuttaṃ (3) (s1) | tatiyadevasuttaṃ (s2, s3) | devā (3) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.13:0.3"
msgid "13. Mahālisutta "
msgstr "13. With Mahāli "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn11.13:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn11.13:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.13:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho mahāli licchavī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahāli licchavī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Mahāli the Licchavi went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn11.13:2.1"
msgid "“Diṭṭho kho, bhante, bhagavatā sakko devānamindo”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, have you seen Sakka, lord of gods?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn11.13:3.1"
msgid "“Diṭṭho kho me, mahāli, sakko devānamindo”ti. "
msgstr "“I have, Mahāli.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn11.13:4.1"
msgid "“So hi nūna, bhante, sakkapatirūpako bhavissati. "
msgstr "“But surely, sir, you must have seen someone who looked like Sakka. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:4.2"
msgid "Duddaso hi, bhante, sakko devānamindo”ti. "
msgstr "For Sakka is hard to see.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn11.13:5.1"
msgid "“Sakkañca khvāhaṃ, mahāli, pajānāmi sakkakaraṇe ca dhamme, yesaṃ dhammānaṃ samādinnattā sakko sakkattaṃ ajjhagā, tañca pajānāmi. "
msgstr "“Mahāli, I understand Sakka. And I understand the things that he undertook and committed to, which enabled him to achieve the status of Sakka. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.496, sc6
msgctxt "sn11.13:6.1"
msgid "Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo pubbe manussabhūto samāno magho nāma māṇavo ahosi, tasmā maghavāti vuccati. "
msgstr "In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he was a brahmanical student named Magha. That’s why he’s called Maghavā. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn11.13:7.1"
msgid "Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo pubbe manussabhūto samāno sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ adāsi, tasmā sakkoti vuccati. "
msgstr "In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he gave gifts carefully. That’s why he’s called Sakka, the careful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn11.13:8.1"
msgid "Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo pubbe manussabhūto samāno pure dānaṃ adāsi, tasmā purindadoti vuccati. "
msgstr "In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he gave gifts in stronghold after stronghold. That’s why he’s called Purindada, the stronghold-giver. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn11.13:9.1"
msgid "Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo pubbe manussabhūto samāno āvasathaṃ adāsi, tasmā vāsavoti vuccati. "
msgstr "In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he gave the gift of a guest house. That’s why he’s called Vāsava, the houser. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn11.13:10.1"
msgid "Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo sahassampi atthānaṃ muhuttena cinteti, tasmā sahassakkhoti vuccati. "
msgstr "Sakka thinks of a thousand things in a moment. That’s why he’s called Sahassakkha, Thousand-Eye. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn11.13:11.1"
msgid "Sakkassa, mahāli, devānamindassa sujā nāma asurakaññā pajāpati, tasmā sujampatīti vuccati. "
msgstr "Sakka’s wife is the demon maiden named Sujā. That’s why he’s called Sujampati, Sujā’s husband. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.231, sc12
msgctxt "sn11.13:12.1"
msgid "Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ issariyādhipaccaṃ rajjaṃ kāreti, tasmā devānamindoti vuccati. "
msgstr "Sakka rules as sovereign lord over the gods of the Thirty-Three. That’s why he’s called lord of gods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.497, sc13
msgctxt "sn11.13:13.1"
msgid "Sakkassa, mahāli, devānamindassa pubbe manussabhūtassa satta vatapadāni samattāni samādinnāni ahesuṃ, yesaṃ samādinnattā sakko sakkattaṃ ajjhagā. "
msgstr "In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he undertook seven vows. And it was because of undertaking these that he achieved the status of Sakka. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.2"
msgid "Katamāni satta vatapadāni? "
msgstr "What seven? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.13:13.3"
msgid "Yāvajīvaṃ mātāpettibharo assaṃ, "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I support my parents. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.4"
msgid "yāvajīvaṃ kule jeṭṭhāpacāyī assaṃ, "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I honor the elders in the family. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.5"
msgid "yāvajīvaṃ saṇhavāco assaṃ, "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I speak gently. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.6"
msgid "yāvajīvaṃ apisuṇavāco assaṃ, "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I not speak divisively. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.7"
msgid "yāvajīvaṃ vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvaseyyaṃ muttacāgo payatapāṇi vossaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato, "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I live at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to give and to share. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.8"
msgid "yāvajīvaṃ saccavāco assaṃ, "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I speak the truth. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.9"
msgid "yāvajīvaṃ akkodhano assaṃ—sacepi me kodho uppajjeyya, khippameva naṃ paṭivineyyanti. "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I be free of anger, or should anger arise, may I quickly get rid of it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.13:13.10"
msgid "Sakkassa, mahāli, devānamindassa pubbe manussabhūtassa imāni satta vatapadāni samattāni samādinnāni ahesuṃ, yesaṃ samādinnattā sakko sakkattaṃ ajjhagāti. "
msgstr "In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he undertook seven vows. And it was because of undertaking these that he achieved the status of Sakka. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn11.13:14.1"
msgid "Mātāpettibharaṃ jantuṃ, "
msgstr "A person who respects their parents, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:14.2"
msgid "kule jeṭṭhāpacāyinaṃ; "
msgstr "and honors the elders in the family, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:14.3"
msgid "Saṇhaṃ sakhilasambhāsaṃ, "
msgstr "whose speech is gentle and courteous, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:14.4"
msgid "pesuṇeyyappahāyinaṃ. "
msgstr "and has given up divisiveness; "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn11.13:15.1"
msgid "Maccheravinaye yuttaṃ, "
msgstr "who’s committed to getting rid of stinginess, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:15.2"
msgid "saccaṃ kodhābhibhuṃ naraṃ; "
msgstr "is truthful, and has mastered anger: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:15.3"
msgid "Taṃ ve devā tāvatiṃsā, "
msgstr "the gods of the Thirty-Three "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:15.4"
msgid "āhu sappuriso itī”ti. "
msgstr "call them truly a good person.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
